Overview

This report highlights the rising prevalence of cyber threats in 2025, with a focus on phishing, ransomware, and password-related attacks.

The analysis indicates that human error remains the primary cause of security breaches, underscoring the need for continuous awareness training and proactive cybersecurity measures.

Recommendations

Implement and enforce strong password policies.

Conduct quarterly cybersecurity training for all staff and students.

Ensure regular backups of critical systems to prevent data loss.
